data.description:
1: US Senator Lummis's new Bitcoin bill requires a stricter purchase plan and uses the gold revaluation proceeds to buy Bitcoin;
2: Alliance DAO founder: ETH is currently severely oversold, it is hard not to want to buy;
3: USDT on-chain activity hit a 6-month high, and traders may be ready to buy at the bottom;
4: Vitalik: Ethereum's goal has never been unclear, and Ethereum's goal is to attract a large number of users;
5: Argentine lawyers apply for an international arrest warrant to hunt down Hayden Davis, the core figure of the Libra scandal;
6: South Korea plans to lift the ban on institutional investors investing in crypto assets in Q3;
7: Ledger assists competitor Trezor in fixing hardware wallet security vulnerabilities;
8: Ripple obtains a license from the Dubai Financial Services Authority to provide crypto payment services in the UAE;
9: Bitcoin spot ETF had a total net inflow of US$13.3326 million yesterday, and Ethereum spot ETF had a total net outflow of US$10.4023 million yesterday;
10: nunu.ai completes a US$6 million seed round of financing, TIRTA Ventures and a16z speedrun co-led the investment;
11: A whale lost $6.62 million in 15 days and then deposited 5,000 ETH to Binance;
12: A whale hoarded $3.66 million in WIF, with a floating profit of $225,000;
13: An ETH whale liquidated 6,401 ETH, with a loss of $1.974 million;
14: Nansen supports multi-token staking to obtain points, and the balance of points will be launched in Q2;
15: Virtuals Protocol announced the launch of the multi-agent framework ACP;
16: 99.2% of the new shares of Trump's encryption project WLFI have been sold.
